snippet.textDisplay:
FACE OF AUSTRALIA: It is sacred to us through Novak for "Rio Tinto"!
SOURCE: M. J. - K. I. - 08.01.2022 | 20:00

Prime Minister Scott Morrison's chief of staff worked for a company whose lithium mine project in Jadro is far from being realized.The ties of the Prime Minister of Australia Scott Morrison and his cabinet with the Australian-British company "Rio Tinto" could be the main, but not the only cause of all the troubles that the world's greatest tennis player Novak Djokovic has been going through in recent days.

The fact that John Kankel, the head of Morrison's cabinet, worked for "Rio Tinto" speaks of revenge on Nolet personally, but also on the state of Serbia because he got stuck in the project in Jadro. Namely, from 2016 to 2018, he was the head of the department for cooperation with the Australian government, and in 2018 he moved to the Prime Minister's Office. That is why there are more and more comments that Djokovic is only a collateral damage of the conflict of interests of these two, because the Prime Minister five years ago fiercely protested against the increase in the tax on iron ore, which, among others, was extracted by "Rio Tinto".

snippet.textDisplay:
In my opinion this case is going exactly what could have been expected: Djokovic being the media icon that he is posing and parading on social media how great the world is and how everything is going his way - here I come Australia ... Surely many people - most of all Australians who are still suffering no travel situation - took a very critical look at this and voiced their discontent. Who would not. In a country whose citizens believe in equality.  Sure the PM jumped on this opportunity to repair whatever he could for his own government and reputation.
Djokovic on the other hand does not seem to see this. For him - as usual - it is only about himself. It is he in the centre of attention.
